INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '92280fbc-302b-4517-b189-8f54219a06f1',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Spark Orchestration Patterns — Fan-Out/Fan-In, Dynamic Task Mapping, and Conditional Branches$escape$,
  $escape$Spark's DAG execution model enables sophisticated orchestration without an external scheduler. Fan-out happens naturally when you call `flatMap` or `explode` to emit multiple output records per input, then chain downstream transformations — each partition processes independently. Fan-in uses `union`, `join`, or `reduceByKey` to collapse distributed results back into a unified dataset.

Dynamic task mapping in Spark means parameterizing jobs at runtime using input metadata. Read a manifest DataFrame listing S3 paths, then use `foreachPartition` or a loop over `collect()`'d configs to dispatch per-source read/transform pipelines. For true dynamic parallelism, pair this with `spark.sparkContext.parallelize(configs).flatMap(process)` so Spark schedules work across executors rather than the driver.

Conditional branches use DataFrame filter splits: `val hot = df.filter($"temp" > 90); val cold = df.filter($"temp" <= 90)`. Each branch materializes independently — cache the parent with `df.persist(StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK)` before splitting to avoid recomputation. Use `df.explain(true)` to verify Spark isn't re-scanning the source twice when branch predicates are non-overlapping.$escape$,
  $escape$val manifest = spark.read.json("s3://bucket/manifest/*.json")
val configs = manifest.collect().map(r => (r.getString(0), r.getString(1)))

val results = spark.sparkContext
  .parallelize(configs, numSlices = configs.length)
  .flatMap { case (path, schema) =>
    spark.read.schema(schema).parquet(path)
      .filter($"event_type" === "click")
      .toLocalIterator
  }

val unified = spark.createDataFrame(results, outputSchema)
unified.persist(StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK)

val critical = unified.filter($"severity" === "P0")
val standard = unified.filter($"severity" =!= "P0")

critical.write.mode("overwrite").parquet("s3://bucket/critical/")
standard.write.mode("overwrite").parquet("s3://bucket/standard/")$escape$,
  $escape$kotlin$escape$,
